development.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Side By Side Content</title><link>/reference/markdown/side-by-side-conten/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/reference/markdown/side-by-side-conten/</guid><description>&lt;p>A shortcode is available (&lt;code>{{% sidebyside %}}&lt;/code>) in order to have content, within a single file, in two different columns that are side by side.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Create side-by-side content by using the following:&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>




&amp;lt;div class=&amp;#34;side-by-side&amp;#34;&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;div style=&amp;#34;float:left; width:50%&amp;#34;&amp;gt;
 

Content you want on the left hand side of the site


&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;div style=&amp;#34;float:right; width:50%&amp;#34;&amp;gt;
 

Content you want on the right hand side of the site


&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Note&lt;/strong>: &lt;code>--split-content--&lt;/code> is where the content is to be split between left and right. Without this keyword the site will fail to render the two columns correctly&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>